This locus was designated for the removal of soil containing the fill debris and sediment between Loci 2, 3, and 7 to the east. The soil was of sandy consistency and is pale red in color (Munsell Pale Red10R 6/3). There was not much cultural material, however, it can be noted that as the excavation progressed, colored stucco with deep lime, salmon and ocher colors was found fallen away from the walls indicating that this was an elegant entryway into the so-called Baths and the West Cryptoporticus.
Closing elevation: At the elevation of the Locus 12 Entry Level Platform.
All constructed locithe upper steps the lower steps and the platforms between them.
Possible earlier excavated deposits that have now been removed.
